South East Governors will meet in Owerri, the Imo State capital to deliberate on security- related issues today.  Also expected at the meeting are the Brigade Commanders, Navy, Air Force Commanders, Inspector General of Police, Ohanaeze Ndigbo and other stakeholders. Read Also: How to tackle insecurity, by OkorochaThe Governors, according to sources, are meeting to find solution to the recent insecurity challenges facing the zone, particularly the recent jail break and attack on Imo Police headquarters that led to release of over 600 suspects in police custody and 1,881 inmates at the Correctional Service Centre Owerri. Chief Press Secretary to Imo Governor, Oguike Nwachuku confirmed the meeting. He said the governors would brief the media after the meeting. Details shortly… By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - After the attach by unknown gunmen on Police headquartets in the state, Imo State Governor, Hope Uzodinma and heads of security agencies are currently in an emergency security meeting at the Government House, Owerri. The meeting is coming few hours after unknown gunmen… In "Top Stories" Less than 24 hours after gunmen attacked the Imo State Police Command headquarters and the Nigerian Correctional Service at Owerri, the immediate past Inspector General of Police, Muhammed Adamu, on Tuesday, visited the state. During the visit, the ex-IG insisted that members of the Indigenous People of Biafra carried out… In "News" IMO State Governor, Hope Uzodinma, says aggrieved politicians in the country are sponsoring a “national crisis” in states controlled by the ruling All Progressives Congress in the South-East geo-political zone. Specifically, the governor said APC detractors were determined to bring down the regime of the President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari… In "Politics"